The paper deals with pricing mechanisms and strategic recommending in social networks, which are topics that fall under game theory and social computing. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also touches upon anonymity and privacy issues, which could place it under cs.CY (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the phenomenon of "banner blindness", which is related to human-computer interaction and could potentially place it under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
